{"title_page": "The War Doctor (audio drama series)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2016}}\n<!-- [[Template:Infobox audio drama]] isn't quite right for an audio drama series, using as best I can for now -->\n{{Infobox audio drama\n|title              = The War Doctor\n|cover              = Doctor Who The War Doctor Volume 1.jpg\n|publisher          = [[Big Finish Productions]]\n|series = Doctor Who\n|featuring          = [[War Doctor]]\n|writer             = various\n|starring             = [[John Hurt]]\n|director           = [[Nicholas Briggs]]\n|music              = Howard Carter\n|producer           = David Richardson\n|executive_producer =  {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jason Haigh-Ellery]]\n* Nicholas Briggs\n}}\n|date               = {{Start date|2015|12|df=y}} \u2013 {{End date|2017|2|df=y}}\n}}\n'''''The War Doctor''''', announced in October 2015, is a [[Big Finish Productions]] [[audio play]] series based on the TV show ''[[Doctor Who]]''. It sees the return of Sir [[John Hurt]] as the [[War Doctor]], a role he previously portrayed in the TV story \"[[The Name of the Doctor]]\" as well as more prominently in the 50th Anniversary special \"[[The Day of the Doctor]]\". The series consists of four box sets, each made up of three hour-long episodes, the first released in December 2015, the remaining three volumes followed across 2016 and into 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctor Who: The War Doctor|url=http://www.bigfinish.com/news/v/doctor-who-the-war-doctor|publisher=[[Big Finish Productions]]|date=5 October 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"WarDoc\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/reehines/2015/10/05/doctor-who-john-hurt-to-return-as-the-war-doctor-in-new-stories/ |title=Doctor Who? John Hurt To Return As The War Doctor In New Stories |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=5 October 2015 |website=[[Forbes]] |publisher= [[Forbes]] |access-date=3 May 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[John Hurt|Sir John Hurt]] as [[The Doctor (Doctor Who)|The War Doctor]]\n*[[Jacqueline Pearce]] as Cardinal Ollistra\n*[[Nicholas Briggs]] as [[Dalek|The Daleks]]\n*[[Dan Starkey]] as General Fesk / [[Sontaran|The Sontarans]] ''(series 3)''\n*[[Louise Jameson]] as [[Leela (Doctor Who)|The Lady / Leela]] ''(series 4)''\n\n==Episodes==\nThe War Doctor faces the Daleks in four seasons of the Time War.\n===Series 1: ''Only the Monstrous'' (2015)===\n<section begin=series1 />{{Episode table |background=#321C16 |overall=5 |title=25 |director=15 |writer=15 |aux3=25 |airdate=15 |aux3T=Featuring |airdateT=Released |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = The Innocent\n| DirectedBy      = Nicholas Briggs\n| WrittenBy       = Nicholas Briggs\n| Aux2            = Rejoice, Ollistra\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|12|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = The Doctor is discovered injured on the planet Keska and is nursed back to health by Rejoice. The planet comes under attack from an enemy and the Doctor assists with the defence.\n| LineColor       = 321C16\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = The Thousand Worlds\n| DirectedBy      = Nicholas Briggs\n| WrittenBy       = Nicholas Briggs\n| Aux2            = Rejoice, Ollistra\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|12|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 321C16\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = The Heart of the Battle\n| DirectedBy      = Nicholas Briggs\n| WrittenBy       = Nicholas Briggs\n| Aux2            = Rejoice, Ollistra\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|12|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 321C16\n}}\n}}<section end=series1 />\n\n===Series 2: ''Infernal Devices'' (2016)===\n<section begin=series2 />{{Episode table |background=#321C16 |overall=5 |title=25 |director=15 |writer=15 |aux3=25 |airdate=15 |aux3T=Featuring |air