ht of the Doctor]]\").\n\nThe series consists of four box sets, each made up of four hour-long episodes, the first was released in October 2017<ref name=\"WarDoc\" />, the remaining three volumes follow yearly from 2018.\n\n===Cast===\n*[[Paul McGann]] as [[Eighth Doctor|The Doctor]]\n*[[Nicholas Briggs]] as [[Dalek|The Daleks]]\n*[[Rakhee Thakrar]] as Bliss\n*[[Jacqueline Pearce]] as Cardinal Ollistra ''(series 1-2)''\n*[[Julia McKenzie]] as The Twelve ''(series 2)''\n*[[Adele Anderson]] as Major Tamasan ''(series 3-4)''\n*[[Michael Jayston]] as [[The Valeyard]] ''(series 3)''\n*[[Terry Molloy]] as [[Davros]] ''(series 4)''\n*[[Ken Bones]] as The General ''(series 4)''\n\n===Episodes===\n====Series 1 (2017)====\n<section begin=special1 />{{Episode table |background=#CEBAD2 |overall=5 |title=25 |director=15 |writer=15 |aux3=25 |airdate=15 |aux3T=Featuring |airdateT=Released |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = The Starship of Theseus\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = John Dorney\n| Aux2            = Sheena, Bliss, Daleks\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Echoes of War\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = Matt Fitton\n| Aux2            = Bliss, Daleks\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = The Conscript\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = Matt Fitton\n| Aux2            = Bliss, Ollistra, Daleks\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| Title           = One Life\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = John Dorney\n| Aux2            = Bliss, Ollistra, Daleks\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n}}<section end=special1 />\n\n====Series 2 (2018)====\n\nThis was the final box set to feature [[Jacqueline Pearce]] as Ollistra before her death in September 2018.\n\n<section begin=special2 />{{Episode table |background=#CEBAD2 |overall=5 |title=25 |director=15 |writer=15 |aux3=25 |airdate=15 |aux3T=Featuring |airdateT=Released |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = The Lords of Terror\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = Jonathan Morris\n| Aux2            = Bliss, Daleks\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|7}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Planet of the Ogrons\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = Guy Adams\n| Aux2            = Bliss, Daleks, the Twelve, [[Ogrons]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|7}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = In the Garden of Death\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = Guy Adams\n| Aux2            = Bliss, Daleks, the Twelve\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|7}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| Title           = Jonah\n| DirectedBy      = Ken Bentley\n| WrittenBy       = Timothy X Atack\n| Aux2            = Bliss, Daleks, Ollistra, the Twelve\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|7}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = CEBAD2\n}}\n}}<section end=special2 />\n\n====Series 3 (2019)====\n<section begin=special3 />{{Episode table |background=#CEBAD2