es]] |access-date=3 May 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[John Hurt|Sir John Hurt]] as [[The Doctor (Doctor Who)|The War Doctor]]\n*[[Jacqueline Pearce]] as Cardinal Ollistra\n*[[Nicholas Briggs]] as [[Dalek|The Daleks]]\n*[[Louise Jameson]] as [[Leela (Doctor Who)|The Lady]] ''(series 4)''\n\n==Episodes==\nThe War Doctor faces the Daleks in four seasons of the Time War.\n===Series 1: ''Only the Monstrous'' (2015)===\n<section begin=series1 />{{Episode table |background=#321C16 |overall=5 |title=25 |director=15 |writer=15 |aux3=25 |airdate=15 |aux3T=Featuring |airdateT=Released |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = The Innocent\n| DirectedBy      = Nicholas Briggs\n| WrittenBy       = Nicholas Briggs\n| Aux2            = Rejoice, Ollistra\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|12|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = The Doctor is discovered injured on the planet Keska and is nursed back to health by Rejoice. The planet comes under attack from an enemy and the Doctor assists with the defence.\n| LineColor       = 321C16\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = The Thousand Worlds\n| DirectedBy      = Nicholas Briggs\n| WrittenBy       = Nicholas Briggs\n| Aux2            = Rejoice, Ollistra\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|12|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 321C16\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The War Doctor (audio drama series)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = The Heart of the Battle\n| DirectedBy      = Nicholas Briggs\n| WrittenBy       = Nicholas Briggs\n| Aux2            = Rejoice, Ollistra\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|12|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 321C16\n}}\n}}<section end=series1 />\n\n===Series 2: ''Infernal Devices'' (2016)===\n<section begin=series2 />{{Episode table |background=#321C16 |overall=5 |title=25 |director=15 |writer=15 |aux3=25 |airdate=15 |aux3T=Feat