723\u2013743 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/41510116 in JSTOR]\n* Rosen, Eliot A. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=KWn5AQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover The Republican Party in the Age of Roosevelt: Sources of Anti-Government Conservatism in the United States]'' (2014)\n* Schneider, Gregory. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=MZ5NWbulMBwC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false The Conservative Century: From Reaction to Revolution]'' (2009)\n* Thorne, Melvin J. ''American Conservative Thought since World War II: The Core Ideas'' (1990) [https://www.questia.com/read/27255773 online edition]\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www.heritage.org/research/lecture/the-origins-of-the-modern-american-conservative-movement \"The Origins of the Modern American Conservative Movement,\"] [[The Heritage Foundation]].\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061010141341/http://www.cerium.ca/article2211.html \"Conservative Predominance in the U.S.: A Moment or an Era?\"], 21 experts from the U.S. and abroad, ponder the future of conservatism.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050404045829/http://etext.lib.virginia.edu/cgi-local/DHI/dhi.cgi?id=dv1-60 ''Dictionary of the History of Ideas: Conservatism'' at the University of Virginia].\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101127222535/http://oah.org/pubs/magazine/conservatism/dickson.html \"Comparative Decades: Conservatism in the 1920s and 1980s\" Lesson plans]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110708020707/http://markriebling.blogs.com/sources_and_methods/a-cr.html Mark Riebling, \"Prospectus for a Critique of Conservative Reason.\"]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100410121117/http://photo.newsweek.com/2010/4/conservative-reactionary-movements.html A History of Conservative Movements] \u2013 slideshow by ''[[Newsweek]]''\n* [http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2015/04/corporate-america-invented-religious-right-conservative-roosevelt-princeton-117030.html How Corporate America Invented Christian America]. Kevin M. 